author: Jack
text: Very nice clean and well organized gym floor. There are 2 levels and feel well spaced out. Not that many cardio machines but it's a gym rat heaven. Many machines that cover all your body needs to train. Plenty of toilets and showers as well in level 2. Aircon is cold and plenty of pigeon holes for your bags too. Only gripe is hard to find parking in this area.

author: Case Woo
text:
Our regular gym has been upgraded with a new look, better lighting and some new equipment. Best fitness group in the world. Shiok.

Happy Halloween!

author: Dee Dee
text:
Update 26 Oct: seems like this branch can't handle feedback well. My husband and I visited couple weeks ago after their refurbishment and was appalled that many of the cardio machines at level 2 not working I.e. treadmill at least 2-3 not functional/stuck, only 1 elliptical machine not working too. Not sure what the branch is upset about with my honest feedback and wanting to report violation. If you can't properly manage the equipment and fix them, then don't be afraid to receive honest feedback from gym goers. I'd now rather visit Marine Parade, Kembangan or Chai Chee branches.

Alot of machines are not working / spoilt at level 2 :(

author: Lucien Lim
text: Spacious, clean, good location, and well-maintained. There is a large function area on the 2nd floor (washrooms are there too). Only caveat is the limited benches available, as well as the small selection of weights. Overall a good branch of AF, great for a regular workout.

author: Kinescape
text: Well equipped & maintained. Very clean too! Level 2 is the functional area. The AC is very cold ü§£. Overall one of the best AF in Singapore that we visited. ‚Ä¶

author: Allan Wooding
text:
Decent location with a good range of equipment and a second floor studio for group classes, functional training and stretching. The staff are very hospitable and I could see clearly they care a lot about the gym users üíï. I had a minor issue with the body scanner (not free by the way) and they reached out to resolve it quickly and ask for feedback. I'm so impressed with the service of the manager I had to update my review to 5 stars.
Be aware though that weights are generally not returned so you might need to run around to get the right weights for some machines. Only 2 free weight racks means you might have a wait when it's busy as well.
Otherwise, good kettlebell range, I like the cushioned floor upstairs, and well placed water coolers.

author: Darren Chee
text: the gym has been newly refreshed and has a bunch of new equipment! dumbbels are now at the 2nd level

author: Benedict Chan
text:
Irons üèãÔ∏è üèãÔ∏è üèãÔ∏è üèãÔ∏è
Cleanliness üêõ üêõ üêõ üêõ
Crowd üßüüßüüßüüßü

Anytime access. Good gym crowd - All purposeful. Towards mature, expat, ladies. Well laid out. Cardios facing wall - with a IG telly CNA. No deadlift station. A little dated and messy but still clean and hygienic. Best AF in East probably.

author: JiaTan
text: Been coming here for more than a year now and am loving the newly renovated place. My personal trainer Faz IS THE BEST and I feel myself progressing so well, she keeps me in check and she's always so helpful and encouraging!!! Thank you Faz!!

author: Adriel T
text: I think this could be the best AF in this area. Can get crowded at times but I supposed it'd be the same with the other outlets. Equipment is well maintained and sufficient even with moderate crowd.

author: Jonny Donlong
text:
What a place! The staff here is such a lad‚Äîsuper friendly, approachable, and always ready with helpful tips or guidance. The trainers are all top-tier professionals who genuinely care about your progress, and it‚Äôs clear they‚Äôre invested in helping you reach your goals. Honestly, what a solid team. The community vibe is amazing, too‚Äîit really feels like you‚Äôre part of something, not just another gym member.

The gym itself is always clean, well-maintained, and well-equipped.

Overall, this gym has everything you need and more to crush your fitness goals. Couldn‚Äôt ask for a better place to train. Highly recommend!

author: Bear Melon
text:
Location 2 (only BuS)
Cleanses 5
Machine variations 2(Life fitness)
Staff 4
Space 3(2nd floor is only for group training)
Free weight 3Racks
good for Back
Shower 3, WC 2(very clean)

author: Lars Foks
text: Awesome gym, very clean, all the equipment you would want and awesome staff, very friendly and welcoming. The atmosphere is very inviting and it‚Äôs not too busy. Best anytime fitness in Singapore!

author: Nicholas Chan
text:
Good quiet gym with friendly staff and people and good equipment
Shout out to David and Joel and JJ ! Friendly and helpful

author: Natasha Anne-Marie
text: Great location and facilities, cleaner than some of the branches I‚Äôve been to. Always a warm space with friendly staff and well-managed programmes. If you‚Äôre looking for a PT, they‚Äôve got an amazing team. Cedrick is one of the trainers who‚Äôs filled with a wealth of knowledge and dedicated to help you achieve your fitness needs! 100% recommend

author: Eileen Lau
text:
The gym and equipment are consistently very clean, which I appreciate!

I also like that they have multiple spacious, clean showers. The small area with hair dryers, mirrors, and a sink is a great touch‚Äîit really completes the post-workout experience. :)

Anytime Fitness Katong is one of my preferred gym to visit.

The only downside is that the strength area can get pretty cramped during peak hours.

author: Titus
text:
Great functional area, very much lacking in strength training area.

One full floor for functional training, spacious and everything is in great condition.

Tiny strength area that is shared with reception and cardio machines. There‚Äôs a total of 2 squat/bench racks and 1 smith machine, sufficient dumbbells but gets pretty packed on a regular weekday.

Would come here for functional training, but AF at Marine Parade for strength.

author: Endro Sunarso
text: Nothing great. Run of the mill gym. Update - However the place is spotlessly clean with very friendly staff -  which makes the difference. Been there at least a dozen times in the past month & it is their staff's happy demeanour & client services that impressed me.

author: Yassy Chan
text:
We were members from another branch of Anytime Fitness, but since we recently moved to the East we started coming here.

The gym has a spacious 1-floor, open layout. The staff was very friendly and they even had personal touches such as Friday snacks. Their fitness class schedule also had a good variety.

In terms of equipment, the machines seem well maintained based on our first few visits. We went in the afternoon and while there were a number of people, it was not too crowded.

We are night owls and so a 24-hour gym that's located with easy access (it's like it's own shop vs inside a mall) definitely helps.

Looking forward to working out here more.

author: Sanae Inada
text: I like this gym! It‚Äôs super clean, organized, and the staff are incredibly friendly. The second-floor workout space is a great addition and I find very useful. Overall, I thoroughly enjoy my visits here. I love my trainer, Faz as well :)

author: J Kek
text:
Very nice gym with a huge functional area and a good selection of equipment. My favourite gym in the area.

Update (8 Sep 24): good to see that the gym is refreshing the layout and adding a deadlift platform. A suggestion to make the gym even better is to consider have another 1-2 squat racks and a glute drive machine

author: nusha dakshyni
text: It‚Äôs at a great location, with good equipments. The free weights and ab mats are on the second floor, which is convenient to end workouts there! As compared to sharing space with the rest of the gym. It might get a little crowded during peak hours. Toilets are clean!

author: Dan J
text:
Well stocked gym with decent space and location. Customer service is average when you speak to them but some of my messages were left unreplied to.

They also said I would be able to be able to use other gyms in the city but for some reason they restricted my account and only rectified once I had asked for a cancellation.

Late payment fees are absurdly priced and frustrating to deal with - I had a card stolen shortly before the scheduled payment and there was no chance to change payment detail in time and no flex on the late payment fee.

Overall, the gym is good but the experiences above have driven me out.

author: Ben Koh
text: AF Tanjong Katong is well equipped and well maintained, with a very spacious functional training area and more than adequate washrooms on the second floor. My only misgiving is that the free weight area is slightly smaller compared to the larger gyms, with only 2 squat racks and one smith machine. That being said, the management has used the space rather adequately and as a seasoned gym goer I can safely say you can get in a pretty good work out for any muscle group of your choice, even if it‚Äôs crowded, with a little patience. Trainers and members are friendly too. Definitely worth a visit.

author: Ace S
text:
Nice, quiet gym that is in a relatively convenient location.

Would also strongly recommend the trainer Faz in particular as she is quite patient and dedicated in getting her trainees to their fitness goals.

Have been on my fitness journey with her and she has motivated me to come for training with her enthusiastic and friendly attitude. But be warned, even though she‚Äôs really nice, her training can be quite tough, so you‚Äôre guaranteed to see results.

author: Jessie Naidu
text: Did an indoor cycling class here, was super challenging but also fun! The gym itself is well equipped and has features that I wish AF's near me have, including a punching bag and a second story that has a high ceiling so that you can jump rope.

author: HuiChun Ni
text: Faz is a very nice trainer who is very patient when training me, especially since I am still recovering from an injury. She is careful to ensure that I do not push myself too hard but still enough to improve my fitness. Look forward to our next session!

author: Hanna Psalms (Hanna)
text:
Equipment: Wide range, cable and machine are there. Set of weights.
Cost : on a higer range than usual.  Offers group classes but sadly 2 out of 3 got last minute cancellation. Staff are friendly.
Access: available 24hours
Location: centre of east coast

author: Andre ye
text: Has all the machines n equipment u need. Friendly staff warmly welcome u when u arrive. The second floor is like a whole different feel! Lovely gym n can see why its so popular. Would be even better if there was maybe one more squat rack or place to do deadlifts as there r quite a lot of ppl during peak period. But ya. Overall one of the anytime fitness gyms that i feel is a must go. =)

author: Gabriela Lim
text: Great space. The 2nd floor is so quiet, and perfect for a good workout. They also have lots of good equipment that other centers do not have. Love it here!

author: Nadiah P
text: It is a newly build double-story gym with a spacious area so you won't feel someone is in your personal space during your workout. They provide a sufficient number of conventional cardio machines and weight-lifting area. Staffs are friendly and ready to answer your questions as needed. In addition to the great interior and the people, I would say the location itself. It is near a bus stop, healthy/delicious food nearby and walking distance to the malls. There may be other gyms around the block, but who doesn't know Anytime Fitness!

author: yDNA W
text: A lovely AF outlet which is spacious and clean! The personal trainers Mick. Dominic and Rudy are super friendly dudes! The club manager William and ambassador Alexson are really fun to talk to.... always sharing with me their jokes and where to find yummy food around the club.. Will definitely come again after my work or during weekends! ^_^

author: Charmailt Ng
text: Nice and spacious place! Before coming in it looks a small but q surprised to see that it‚Äôs well spaced! :) friendly staff here too that‚Äôs helpful

author: Trisha Tan
text: First time visiting this branch and it‚Äôs probably one of my favourite outlets! The gym is well equipped and the second level is very spacious. The staff was friendly, and even pointed out where the lockers and shower rooms were to me :)

author: Abigail Grace
text: Love the gym here, please renovate fast :‚Äô hope to return soon!

author: yizhen
text: thiban is very helpful and answered all my questions, the gym is very spacious and big , there are two storeys and the equipment here is adequate üòä ‚Ä¶

author: Tseng Ying Heng (hyprlapse_)
text: Faz is a very friendly trainer and well knowledged trainer. Prior to joining, she had sat down andd understood my goals before helping to provide a plan to help me achieve these goals. Despite not having any experience going to the gym before, I was able to grasps the basics quickly with her help and work towards my goals.  I would definetely recommend Faz to anyone looking for a trainer to get started on their fitness goals!

author: Dorothy In Singapore
text: This AF Katong is one of the cleanest I've been to, aircon temperature is perfect to workout with and staff are friendly and professionals, the space for mobility and stretching on the 2nd floor is huge and very comfortable to do other workouts

author: Vairavan Ramanathan
text:
I like the arrangement of the gym spacious , easy access right next to bus stop and it has 2 floors. I love the top floor with TRX and rowing machine and space for yoga and stretching.
The staff are friendly and William was very helpful with my assisted pull ups.
Love going to this gym. Since it is spacious you don‚Äôt feel it is packed.

author: Kelly Latimer-Loi
text: Nice space to train in the Joo Chiat hood. Second floor is spacious and well-stocked, great for calisthenics and HIITs. First floor is a little crowded, but can't be helped with big machines. It's got everything you need for a good workout, even if you have to dance around people at times.

author: Gogo Plata
text: Strength and machine area (not that many but usual ones).  Has a deadlift platform and power bars.  Open functional area 2nd lvl is useful.  Very clean.

author: Felicia W
text: Well-equipped and well-maintained. The toilets are also really clean. Wish there were more squat racks because I often have to wait for my turn even for weekdays at timings like 2pm. Otherwise, I‚Äôm satisfied!

author: Stefanie Teguh
text: Great gym in a strategic location. The staff are friendly and accomodating. Equipments are kept clean and well maintained. A special mention goes to the exceptional water pressure which led to a good post-workout shower experience.

author: Jonathan Ball
text:
Clean, friendly staff, and top notch customer service!

Attended this gym during my visit to Singapore. I initially inquired about purchasing a new tag to enter the gym, but was informed there was no need to spend the extra money as I was only there for a couple of weeks. I forgot to ask for the staff member's name, but she had sent an email to the entire team informing them who I was.
The next time I visited the gym, the staff already knew I was a visitor from Australia, and entrance to the gym was as if I was a local, the only difference being I had to ring the doorbell.

Thank you for your hospitality!

Another mention to all the attendees for always keeping the gym clean. Everyone I saw there was diligent in returning weights to their proper places and wiping down equipment after use, something I'm not used to seeing in a large chain gym.

author: Chris Lim
text: Decently stacked gym and great location. Branch manager is also nice and friendly! Has most machines and even a second level for the functional area. Standard 2 power racks and 1 smith, with plenty of machines. I saw a hexagon trap bar too which means you can try trap bar deadlifts. Quite rare to see such equipment in an AF gym.

author: Putri Shakirah
text: my new fave go-to outlet! the layout is awesome, really spacious on both floors, the facilities & equipment are clean. it‚Äôs not crowded when i went there so it‚Äôs a bonus for me, the one outlet i could have access to all the equipment i wanted for my full workout üèãÔ∏è‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è ü§© ‚Ä¶

author: yak ck
text: Asyraf is very clear on his explanation for the gym do and don't.   In general, this branch is very new and well managed.  Gym goers are also very friendly and cultured.  Highly recommended to join!

author: Rainy Mak
text: Very friendly staff! There are limited benches so during peak hours you might have to wait for one. The function area takes up the whole  second floor, good for stretching and mobility work‚ò∫Ô∏è

author: Daniel Chew
text: Place is clean spacious and well maintained. Equipment wise is pretty standard and it hits most the requirements for my training. I do wish they had a machine for hyperextension. But you can have a make shift one on the second for so no complaints either.

author: Zaidi Kamsin
text: Since its a new place definitely all the equipment is clean i witness it myself the gym is looking really great... I cant wait to start using it. hopefully it stays that way. Aside, the service is perfectly fun, Filza explains well and was very clear about the details and she rocks.

author: Cheryl H
text: The gym is clean and well equipped. The staff at the gym are also very friendly. Shout out to Dominic who is a good motivator and even better personal trainer - always pushing me to challenge my limits and improve myself.

author: Yuko Tan
text:
Wonderful and spacious outlet with 2 levels for usage.
Happy to see equipment well-kept in good condition and the location is perfect for grabbing a good cuppa chai/coffee post or pre-workout.

Would love to visit anytime again!

author: Charles Tee
text:
The team in the AF Tanjong Katong team are really friendly and respectful and you can expect a warm greeting every time you come by for a visit. The facilities are well maintained by Subash who ensures that everything is clean and ready for use and William, Alexson and their other team members are there always to give a ready smile and to keep a watchful eye on the members to ensure their welfare and enjoyment.
The personal trainers like Dominic are also ever smiling and friendly and this gym has a friendly neighbourhood vibe like no other. Well done AF TK, keep it up !!

author: Corrine Ng
text: Great personal training experience with Dominic. He is patient and will motivate you to work harder to reach your goals. The gym is fully equipped as well and everyone here is friendly.

author: Rachel Lee
text: Gym has all the necessary equipment and is kept clean. Staff are really helpful - Parthiban, Cedric and William. Only critique is that it can be very full at certain times due to large amount of members.

author: Tan Yan Ni
text: Signed up for a membership with AF Tanjong Katong recently after comparing several gyms around the area. Very spacious with two stories, clean machines and equipments. The staffs are very friendly and attentive as well.

author: Hiyoshi
text:
Top tier AF gym, clean and pretty spacious.

1. Dumbbells go up to 45kg, great knurling on handle, always clean and some weights ( 15 kg, etc ) have 2 pairs which is nice during peak hours.

2. Top tier equipment like Life Fitness and Hammer Strength. Some rare ones too like the Stairmaster and the Plate Loaded Iso Row ( my personal favorite )

3. Clean toilets and showers. There's even hair dryers, same as the AF I went to in Japan a few years back which is nice. Not sure if this is standard across all AF in Singapore but it's always nice to see some personalization.

All in all, great place, nice people, I'd definitely recommend it.

author: Claus
text: Very clean place and in early mornings before work all equipment is available. Has everything needed. When I signed up, staff was very welcoming and helpful.

author: Kyn Marie Tay Wei Jing
text: Clean and spacious gym with plenty of equipments available that are well maintained. Staff are very warm and friendly, always nice to be warmly greeted whenever I drop by the gym during staffed hours :)

author: d t
text: Shout out to Dinesh and Ashraf for a warm welcome! Haven't done much (any?) exercise for a long time and needed to get started. They were amazingly patient in their welcome. Thank you.

author: Christopher Bobin
text: Anytime Fitness Tanjong Katong is located in an area known for Peranakan culture, so the vibe of this neighborhood is different from that which you would get in the typical mall experience in Singapore. As such, this Anytime Fitness offers the chance for an interesting change of scenery as well as a first rate facility for exercise.  When I first walked in for a peek, they had just opened and one of the friendly and courteous staff was happy to show me the facility, which is two floors: On the ground level is most of the weights, machines and aerobic equipment while the second floor is for group classes, etc.  And they have showers!, something lacking in a lot of AF outlets: This is good if you are working out during the day and returning to office.  The scale and scope of equipment is sufficient for any serious weight training.  Afterward, explore the neighborhood as there is an excellent mix of old and new restaurants and food options for that all-important post-workout meal... Highly recommended.

author: Jeremiah Su
text:
Nice and clean! But only has 2 bench racks, so unless you‚Äôre okay with the DB rack, you‚Äôll just have to wait.

Overall very spacious and pretty well lit!

author: Dmitriy Korotaev
text: I‚Äôve been staying near Joo Chiat road for the last 6 months, and I couldn‚Äôt have asked for a better gym than Anytime Fitness Tanjong Katong. It‚Äôs conveniently located, and being open 24 hours is a huge plus. The gym is well-equipped, with everything you need from treadmills to a boxing area and cross fit equipment. I have to give a shoutout to the manager Alexson for being so attentive to details and always willing to help the members. I highly recommend this gym to anyone in the area looking for a great workout spot.

author: Tse yiu fai
text: The gym is clean and well-equipped. Staff are friendly and trainers are knowledgeable. The users are civilised and supportive to each other. A very pleasant experience.

author: Bridget Foo
text: Convenient location and the interior is very clean. There are showers and restrooms facilities, studio is also spacious with lockers. The gym location and facilities very well serve the neighborhood. Plus, we can gym hop to other locations‚Äô and other countries‚Äô ANYTIME.

author: Con Balao
text: Staffs are friendly, they are very accommodating. The place is clean, highly equip gym and they instructor/trainer is awesome. It's fun to had tried out to train here. Recommended

author: Jay Kim
text:
Good location, well maintained facilities.

But very ridiculous that the inbody machine is chargeable at $27 per time.. First time hear in my gym life lol. Firstly was not but suddenly changed?

author: Noel Blancaflor
text: The best branch of AF ever!!! Helpful & friendly staffüëçüëç üëç im actually from the Philippines and i really love your hospitality üòòüòòüòò thanks for the lanyard ‚úåÔ∏è‚úåÔ∏è‚úåÔ∏è ‚Ä¶

author: Rowena Chun
text: Just joined as a new member. So far happy with the staff service, equipment and machine well maintain. Overall comfortable feeling which is very important for one new to gym exercise. One question why Tanjong Katong and not just Katong?  Haha

author: PC Pei
text: I happened to walk past today and found a new Anytime Fitness Gym near my house! I felt like a queen to be served by 4 friendly male staff - Bastian (hopefully I spelled it correctly) Ben, Andy and Dominic. They told me that the 2-storey, 24-hr gym will be opening soon in July which I decided to sign up with them on the spot for the cheaper than usual rate and other free goodies. Can't wait for it to open soon!  Cheers guys!

author: Smita Nigam Mishra
text: This is a wonderful facility in Katong. Equipments are new and place is super clean . Greeted by very friendly Elsa who showed us the facility . Not pushy at all and made me feel so comfortable. Filzah was very responsive when we were exploring the options and very quick in answering our queries . Highly recommended!

author: Q.P.
text: Always clean, and I love having extra space on the second floor to do workouts that don't use a machine. Always plenty of space there to stretch out

author: Bai Yuhui
text: Thiban the owner of the restaurant was extremely friendly and chill. The gym have sufficient equipments, weights, and machines. Would definitely recommend coming down go work out here!

author: Sophia ZHENG
text: It has a dedicated space for cardio training at the upper level. Spacious enough to do plyometrics like broad jumps. Go in the morning if you prefer a quiet workout.

author: Louis Ong
text: Exceptional facilities, clean, well equipped, fulfils all my equipment needs. Shower and bathroom facilities all in superb condition. Transferred to this branch after a year at various others. Opposite also got very good chicken rice.

author: Lyia Halim
text: Elsa the fitness advisor is attentive and approachable. Her friendly gesture encouraged me to feel at ease into deciding the membership application. She assist me through the sign up smoothly and offer help anytime. Look out for Elsa to sign up or queries about the gym!

author: Ploypailin Thomas
text:
After I tried 1 day trial pass, I decided to join the gym because
1. Location; easy to go there by bus and after  workout, we can find something to eat around there
2. The machines; it is friendly for female as well

author: Alive. wp
text: Spacious gym which is good for most fitness practices üëç ‚Ä¶

author: Kenneth Tan
text: amazing outlet! 2 stories, well maintained equipments, alvis was very friendly and approachable too. highly recommended!

author: Simon Tay
text: Great location and cosy outlet. 2 levels with well equipped machines and facilities. Nice studio for group classes on Second floor with indoor bikes for spinning classes.

author: Taro Alexander Nordmark
text: Gym has what you need for a good session, and with 24hr opening times and multiple other locations (available after sign up, and a 1 month grace period) it's a competitive price! Bonus: Staff seem really helpful and kind!

author: Dan MacLachlan
text: Excellent facilities, welcoming staff and a relaxed atmosphere. Right in the heart of Katong this spacious gym is good value and a great place to work out whatever your fitness levels.

author: Marcus Lee
text: Very good vibes, AC is icy, equipment is clean. Plenty of street parking early in the morning. Perfect.

author: Vincent
text: This gym is well kept and very clean (especially the toilets and bathrooms). There‚Äôs a big group exercise area upstairs. The strong AC in the gym is also much appreciated

author: Llewellan Vance
text: Spacious with two floors, modern equipment and friendly crowd. Staff are legends, sourced a piece of equipment I highlighted. One of my favourite Anytimes! ü¶æü´∞üèº ‚Ä¶

author: Quek WeiHeng
text: Cardio machine help to burn my fats. Awesome!

author: David Han_Yue_Xin
text: Nice gym! Cozy, chill and clean

author: B Khoo
text: Awesome place to work out! Place is kept clean, staffs are friendly and approachable. The spinning instructors Roger and Vince are very helpful. Looking forward to more spinning sessions!!

author: Ed Ashley
text:
(1) Location is not too difficult to find which is great (a lot of food places around so pre/mid/post-workout meal is no problem)

(2) 2 stories of space with decent amount of machines, free weights and racks to get you through your workouts

(3) Very clean and comfortable and the music is not bad (personally) so if you do forget your headphones, at least your ears won‚Äôt be bleeding

Thank you Roy for reaching out and great job AF Tanjong Katong, really love the environment you guys have created there.

author: A
text: Unstaffed on a weekday at 9:30am. Tried ringing doorbell a few times and called too. Was looking to do a drop in so we got a grab and drove 18 mins to get here. Very frustrating.

author: Nidhin Bose J.
text:
The responsible people doesn‚Äôt enforce people to train with towel and this makes the place dirty. Imagine how it will make people who bring towel look like.
To Management - please don‚Äôt reply starting ‚Äúwe are sad to ‚Ä¶‚Äù but instead you can ask your team to work on it.
Final Edit: there is no change yet!

author: Mohd Lee
text: Like the location and setup here. One suggestion, please add towels for us to wipe the equipment instead of the paper towel. I seen that done in Bedok and Geylang Bahru branch, it really encourage ppl to wipe after they use. Keep up the good work!

author: Charleston Chan (charlie)
text: it's a nice cute and new gym with everything in near mint quality. accessible  too. the toilet and shower spaces are very secure and clean

author: Black Orchid
text: Clean and spacious gym with well maintained equipment that's more than adequate for most workouts. Shout out to Alexson and William for the warm welcome!

author: Ayrton Ralph
text: Great gym, has all the necessities. My only thing I would say to improve would be for more space to add a few extra machines, but they do well with the current ares.

author: Hassan Sa'eran
text:
Got their contact from their website & inquired through Elsa.

Elsa set up the appointment & it was seamless.

Instantly after the phone call, I received a follow up message from Elsa regarding my appointment.

I received another message from her, to remind me of my appointment the following morning which was great.

I was 20 minutes late for my appointment & informed Elsa, which she referred me to another lady, Filzah, probably because she has somewhere else to be too. Fair enough, since i was late...

Upon arrival, Filzah received me as though i was liaising with her the whole time, which proves that their backend communication was on point & flawless.

Filzah was detailed, patient & answered all my questions without any hiccup. The sign up process was super smooth & swift.

Thank you so much Elsa & Filzah for this flawless experience & recovery. :)

author: Abdul Aziz Bin Zainalabidin
text: My first time applying for AF, and already I'm already am positive about the environment as I was greeted n welcome from the wonderful staff. Can't wait for the official opening and start the progress there !!!

author: Evan King
text:
Great gym, top staff, very clean and tidy. Thank you so much.
Evan

author: Jason Lum
text: Andy and Ben were really prompt and friendly when I happened to pass by the pre-opening fair and made some enquires. The location, surrounding and coupled with great services certainly make it worthwhile to sign up as a member.

author: Elliot Braet
text: Great spacious setup with good variety of equipment, more than a lot of other gyms in the area

author: Lucas Portillo (LUCASPORTILLO.JPEG)
text: Really impressive and friendly staff! All the gym equipment, shower facilities are all in outstanding condition. Really good outlet:)

author: musaddiq Samsudin
text: Gym is clean, conducive and friendly trainers.
